1
00:00:00,760 --> 00:00:03,790
Mihono-chan, happy birthday!
[Mom]

2
00:00:03,790 --> 00:00:07,130
- Thanks!
- If only you'd stayed with Satoshi-kun.

3
00:00:07,130 --> 00:00:10,110
Why did you break up with such a nice guy?

4
00:00:10,110 --> 00:00:12,540
Starting today, I'm joining the sales department.

5
00:00:12,540 --> 00:00:14,260
I'm Eisei Ureshino.

6
00:00:14,260 --> 00:00:16,970
Don't you feel like this is fate?

7
00:00:16,970 --> 00:00:21,240
Reunion sex with the man
I cheated with 10 years ago.

8
00:00:21,240 --> 00:00:23,030
Welcome, Ureshino-kun!

9
00:00:23,030 --> 00:00:24,550
Cheers!

10
00:00:24,550 --> 00:00:27,650
Well, whatever.

11
00:00:33,440 --> 00:00:35,952
What about the second round?

12
00:00:35,952 --> 00:00:38,330
Want to ditch this together?

13
00:00:39,990 --> 00:00:41,475
Let's go.

14
00:00:41,475 --> 00:00:43,800
Huh? Wait!

15
00:00:43,800 --> 00:00:47,580
♫ It's hard to resist the thing
that I've missed for so long ♫

16
00:00:47,580 --> 00:00:49,440
♫ So long ♫

17
00:00:49,440 --> 00:00:53,200
♫ Can't remember what it's like,
just remember I need it ♫

18
00:00:53,200 --> 00:00:55,680
♫ I need it ♫

19
00:00:55,680 --> 00:01:00,030
♫ You're not what I thought you were ♫

20
00:01:00,030 --> 00:01:01,840
♫ You were ♫

21
00:01:01,840 --> 00:01:05,270
♫ To think I can't find a cure ♫

22
00:01:05,270 --> 00:01:07,830
♫ Find a cure ♫

23
00:01:07,830 --> 00:01:13,860
♫ Ooh, you're not what I thought ♫

24
00:01:16,920 --> 00:01:24,380
[If Only You Weren't the One]

25
00:01:24,380 --> 00:01:30,510
[Episode 2]

26
00:02:01,893 --> 00:02:05,859
Well, my train station's this way.

27
00:02:05,859 --> 00:02:08,028
- Bye.
- Huh?

28
00:02:24,210 --> 00:02:26,630
You're so cute, Miporin.

29
00:02:30,640 --> 00:02:32,830
You chased after me.

30
00:02:34,680 --> 00:02:36,780
You tested me?

31
00:02:37,726 --> 00:02:40,595
You're the worst.

32
00:02:40,595 --> 00:02:43,240
You were testing me first, weren't you?

33
00:02:43,240 --> 00:02:45,399
Standing there all alone, staring outside.

34
00:02:45,399 --> 00:02:47,852
- No way.
- Oh.

35
00:02:49,470 --> 00:02:51,620
Were you waiting for me?

36
00:02:53,275 --> 00:02:55,740
Of course not.

37
00:02:55,740 --> 00:02:57,920
I was just resting.

38
00:02:59,000 --> 00:03:01,080
Oh?

39
00:03:02,250 --> 00:03:06,600
I really hate this man.

40
00:03:06,600 --> 00:03:08,830
I hate him so much.

41
00:03:18,340 --> 00:03:20,700
We're kind of...

42
00:03:22,910 --> 00:03:25,380
a special pair, aren't we?

43
00:03:47,690 --> 00:03:50,760
Stop, we're in public.

44
00:03:53,870 --> 00:03:56,090
Does it matter?

45
00:04:49,750 --> 00:04:51,360
Going home?

46
00:04:55,060 --> 00:04:57,500
I don't mind either way.

47
00:05:02,915 --> 00:05:06,240
Oh, it might be smaller than I thought.

48
00:05:06,240 --> 00:05:07,780
Huh?

49
00:05:08,645 --> 00:05:10,600
Oh, you're right.

50
00:05:10,600 --> 00:05:12,395
Well, whatever.

51
00:05:12,395 --> 00:05:16,545
It's better this way, right?

52
00:05:18,950 --> 00:05:21,910
What is this situation?

53
00:05:29,205 --> 00:05:32,480
Do you always bring dates
to places like this?

54
00:05:32,480 --> 00:05:34,040
No.

55
00:05:34,040 --> 00:05:36,690
I mean, I'm not dating anyone.

56
00:05:36,690 --> 00:05:38,625
Oh?

57
00:05:38,625 --> 00:05:41,505
Well, me neither.

58
00:05:41,505 --> 00:05:43,770
Why am I acting like this?

59
00:05:43,770 --> 00:05:45,620
What's with the act?

60
00:05:45,620 --> 00:05:48,455
I'm not putting on an act.

61
00:05:48,455 --> 00:05:51,225
You're so cute, Miporin.

62
00:05:55,656 --> 00:05:57,256
Oh.

63
00:05:59,125 --> 00:06:01,170
Oh, you remember this?

64
00:06:01,170 --> 00:06:04,155
I brought it to read the rest with you.

65
00:06:04,155 --> 00:06:06,530
That's the one that traumatized me!
[The Cage of Night Howling]

66
00:06:06,530 --> 00:06:08,168
How nostalgic.

67
00:06:08,168 --> 00:06:11,343
- Oh, really?
- Yes, really.

68
00:06:12,825 --> 00:06:15,395
- I'm not reading it!
- Oh, hey, look!

69
00:06:15,395 --> 00:06:16,670
See? Isn't this insane?

70
00:06:16,670 --> 00:06:17,670
Look.

71
00:06:17,670 --> 00:06:20,220
- Hey, come on, stop it.
- Wait, this part is fine.

72
00:06:20,220 --> 00:06:22,560
It goes like this, okay?

73
00:06:22,560 --> 00:06:25,190
Look at this. See?

74
00:06:26,055 --> 00:06:28,050
- Come on, I said no!
- Is this too much for you?

75
00:06:28,050 --> 00:06:29,780
Yeah.

76
00:06:32,400 --> 00:06:33,810
Hmm?

77
00:07:00,942 --> 00:07:05,120
I think I like you.

78
00:07:15,776 --> 00:07:18,356
You're so cute, Miporin.

79
00:07:26,410 --> 00:07:28,600
That was a mistake.

80
00:07:34,042 --> 00:07:38,802
I never should have said those words.

81
00:07:50,995 --> 00:07:53,720
Hey, Miporin, want something to drink?

82
00:07:53,720 --> 00:07:55,550
Oh...

83
00:07:55,550 --> 00:07:57,370
Sure.

84
00:07:58,340 --> 00:07:59,870
Huh?

85
00:08:14,253 --> 00:08:16,283
Give me a bite.

86
00:08:21,240 --> 00:08:24,760
It'll spill if you eat it
while lying down, won't it?

87
00:08:28,260 --> 00:08:29,670
Here.

88
00:08:31,720 --> 00:08:34,340
See?

89
00:08:53,720 --> 00:08:57,430
This isn't the place to do it, you know.

90
00:08:58,916 --> 00:09:04,130
This isn't the place to do it, but...

91
00:09:09,380 --> 00:09:11,340
Should we do it?

92
00:09:13,150 --> 00:09:15,080
Or not?

93
00:09:16,816 --> 00:09:18,556
I...

94
00:09:19,610 --> 00:09:21,710
want to.

95
00:09:21,710 --> 00:09:25,530
Aw, man.

96
00:09:25,530 --> 00:09:27,450
What a shame.

97
00:09:29,600 --> 00:09:32,390
I don't want to go home.

98
00:09:33,870 --> 00:09:36,950
I have to get up early tomorrow.

99
00:09:38,580 --> 00:09:40,700
Oh, really?

100
00:09:48,650 --> 00:09:50,850
Wait...

101
00:10:18,930 --> 00:10:20,360
Hey.

102
00:10:25,460 --> 00:10:27,780
Touch me, too.

103
00:10:56,000 --> 00:10:57,650
We can't.

104
00:10:59,870 --> 00:11:01,770
That's sexy.

105
00:11:25,540 --> 00:11:27,300
Should we head home?

106
00:11:27,940 --> 00:11:29,210
Yeah.

107
00:11:36,229 --> 00:11:39,390
It's already past 2 a.m.

108
00:11:39,390 --> 00:11:41,261
- Early morning, right?
- Yeah.

109
00:11:41,261 --> 00:11:43,491
It'll be fine.

110
00:11:44,450 --> 00:11:49,940
Wait, so it's been two whole days
since we reunited?

111
00:11:49,940 --> 00:11:51,385
Oh, right.

112
00:11:51,385 --> 00:11:53,450
I guess so.

113
00:11:53,450 --> 00:11:55,135
About 40 hours.

114
00:11:55,135 --> 00:11:56,645
Yeah.

115
00:11:59,319 --> 00:12:02,310
Even at this age,

116
00:12:02,310 --> 00:12:06,460
this might be the first time
I stayed up this late with someone.

117
00:12:08,926 --> 00:12:10,586
Me too.

118
00:12:29,716 --> 00:12:38,706
So, we're just going to crash here, huh?

119
00:12:38,706 --> 00:12:40,970
Well...

120
00:12:40,970 --> 00:12:42,780
see you tomorrow.

121
00:12:44,110 --> 00:12:46,710
Oh, that's already in five hours.

122
00:12:49,068 --> 00:12:51,110
You're right.

123
00:12:51,110 --> 00:12:53,290
See you tomorrow.

124
00:12:53,290 --> 00:12:54,690
Bye.

125
00:13:01,960 --> 00:13:05,870
Once you set foot in, you...

126
00:13:18,704 --> 00:13:20,535
can't get back out.

127
00:13:30,350 --> 00:13:33,270
It's been two days, huh?

128
00:13:53,159 --> 00:13:56,009
I'm so tired.

129
00:14:12,107 --> 00:14:13,630
Huh?

130
00:14:13,630 --> 00:14:15,650
Can I post it?

131
00:14:15,650 --> 00:14:18,877
Hey, stop that.

132
00:14:18,877 --> 00:14:21,950
Stop it already.

133
00:14:24,250 --> 00:14:27,470
Oh, Satoshi-kun got married.

134
00:14:28,670 --> 00:14:30,200
Look.

135
00:14:32,585 --> 00:14:34,950
You're right.

136
00:14:34,950 --> 00:14:38,160
Good for him.
I'm glad he's happy.

137
00:14:40,090 --> 00:14:42,470
Oh, sorry.

138
00:14:48,555 --> 00:14:50,280
I apologized.

139
00:14:50,280 --> 00:14:53,515
It's fine. I don't deserve an apology.

140
00:14:53,515 --> 00:14:55,325
That's true.

141
00:14:59,560 --> 00:15:00,960
Oh.

142
00:15:04,550 --> 00:15:06,210
Sorry.

143
00:15:07,050 --> 00:15:09,690
It's fine.

144
00:15:09,690 --> 00:15:10,930
Wait, Mihono.

145
00:15:10,930 --> 00:15:13,630
Did you already get a message
about the marriage?

146
00:15:13,630 --> 00:15:17,910
Of course not. I just found out now.

147
00:15:17,910 --> 00:15:19,600
Oh?

148
00:15:21,050 --> 00:15:22,800
Why?

149
00:15:23,966 --> 00:15:28,006
Well, you just look worn out today.

150
00:15:29,430 --> 00:15:31,150
Do I?

151
00:15:34,173 --> 00:15:35,673
Huh? What?

152
00:15:36,693 --> 00:15:38,480
What is it?

153
00:15:39,213 --> 00:15:40,900
Inflation?

154
00:15:41,635 --> 00:15:44,070
Is that why?

155
00:15:44,070 --> 00:15:46,250
If it were that,
I'd have looked like this way sooner.

156
00:15:46,250 --> 00:15:48,248
Then, it's something recent.

157
00:15:48,248 --> 00:15:50,618
Hmm, I wonder what it is.

158
00:15:55,105 --> 00:15:56,540
Is it Eisei Ureshino?

159
00:15:56,540 --> 00:15:59,360
That's creepily specific.

160
00:15:59,360 --> 00:16:01,460
Maki-chan, I might want to cut ties with you.

161
00:16:01,460 --> 00:16:02,900
Ugh...

162
00:16:02,900 --> 00:16:04,685
Are you seeing him again?

163
00:16:04,685 --> 00:16:07,417
He just joined our company.

164
00:16:07,417 --> 00:16:09,077
Seriously?

165
00:16:11,765 --> 00:16:14,220
What is this? You're cursed.

166
00:16:14,220 --> 00:16:16,350
Straight onto
the friends-with-benefits highway!

167
00:16:16,350 --> 00:16:18,810
Did you two meet in a past life?

168
00:16:18,810 --> 00:16:20,180
Maki-chan, quiet.

169
00:16:20,180 --> 00:16:21,845
- Jeez.
- Huh?

170
00:16:21,845 --> 00:16:24,860
So, what are you going to do?

171
00:16:24,860 --> 00:16:27,750
I'm not going to do anything.

172
00:16:43,325 --> 00:16:45,090
Mihono-san, good morning!

173
00:16:45,090 --> 00:16:46,540
Good morning, Yuri-chan!

174
00:16:46,540 --> 00:16:49,140
Huh? You seem different today somehow.

175
00:16:49,140 --> 00:16:51,270
You noticed?

176
00:16:51,270 --> 00:16:53,811
- So cute! You got ribbons?
- Ribbons. Yeah.

177
00:16:53,811 --> 00:16:55,082
- Wow.
- Did them this morning.

178
00:16:55,082 --> 00:16:57,297
- By yourself?
- Yes.

179
00:16:58,585 --> 00:17:00,590
Oh, Ureshino-san!

180
00:17:00,590 --> 00:17:02,365
- Good morning.
- Good morning.

181
00:17:02,365 --> 00:17:04,645
Good morning.

182
00:17:09,025 --> 00:17:13,160
Oh, why weren't you
at the after-party, Ureshino-san?

183
00:17:13,160 --> 00:17:14,277
Oh, I had a thing.

184
00:17:14,277 --> 00:17:16,020
Was it a date or something like that?

185
00:17:16,020 --> 00:17:18,570
It wasn't really a date.

186
00:17:18,570 --> 00:17:21,880
I just had a bit of a fever.

187
00:17:21,880 --> 00:17:23,060
Oh, a cold?

188
00:17:23,060 --> 00:17:25,040
No, I think it was nerves.

189
00:17:25,040 --> 00:17:26,479
I hadn't slept at all.

190
00:17:26,479 --> 00:17:29,935
Really? Ureshino-san, you're adorable.

191
00:17:29,935 --> 00:17:32,650
Well, everyone's nice,
so you'll get used to it soon.

192
00:17:32,650 --> 00:17:36,545
Right. Thank you.

193
00:17:36,545 --> 00:17:38,530
I'll stop by the meeting room first.

194
00:17:38,530 --> 00:17:40,510
Okay, see you later.

195
00:17:44,600 --> 00:17:48,270
Seriously, what the heck is this?

196
00:18:09,690 --> 00:18:11,520
Onuma-san.

197
00:18:12,726 --> 00:18:17,040
Sorry to bother you.
Are you busy tonight?

198
00:18:17,040 --> 00:18:18,495
Huh?

199
00:18:18,495 --> 00:18:22,665
If you're free,
maybe we could get dinner together.

200
00:18:25,830 --> 00:18:27,230
Huh?

201
00:18:27,974 --> 00:18:29,870
With me?

202
00:18:29,870 --> 00:18:31,755
Who else would I be talking to?

203
00:18:31,755 --> 00:18:33,480
What?

204
00:18:33,480 --> 00:18:35,980
But why?

205
00:18:35,980 --> 00:18:37,670
Well...

206
00:18:39,060 --> 00:18:42,080
I'm asking you out on a date.

207
00:18:43,503 --> 00:18:45,320
A date?

208
00:18:46,006 --> 00:18:50,645
It's a bit embarrassing
if you say it out loud like that,

209
00:18:50,645 --> 00:18:53,825
but yes.

210
00:18:53,825 --> 00:18:55,250
What?

211
00:18:55,995 --> 00:18:57,340
Oh, sorry.

212
00:18:57,340 --> 00:18:58,590
I'm sorry.

213
00:18:58,590 --> 00:19:01,330
It must have caught you off guard.

214
00:19:01,330 --> 00:19:03,645
Really, any other day is fine, too.

215
00:19:03,645 --> 00:19:07,675
I'd appreciate it if you could just consider it.

216
00:19:11,416 --> 00:19:13,416
Sorry again.

217
00:19:28,194 --> 00:19:30,690
Section Chief, I’ve scheduled a meeting,
so I’m heading out now.

218
00:19:30,690 --> 00:19:32,340
- Right now?
- Yes.

219
00:19:32,340 --> 00:19:35,000
I'll make sure to be back
for the evening meeting.

220
00:19:35,000 --> 00:19:36,935
- Got it.
- I'll be going.

221
00:19:36,935 --> 00:19:38,975
- Take care!
- Bye.

222
00:19:40,414 --> 00:19:45,174
If I could fall for someone
like Kusaka-kun, I'm sure...

223
00:19:47,250 --> 00:19:51,950
I could be happy.

224
00:19:54,446 --> 00:19:58,156
Instead of someone like Eisei Ureshino.

225
00:19:59,030 --> 00:20:02,070
Instead of a man like him.

226
00:20:04,650 --> 00:20:06,300
It's fine.

227
00:20:09,420 --> 00:20:11,940
I have a girlfriend, too.

228
00:20:14,456 --> 00:20:16,286
We can't.

229
00:20:30,310 --> 00:20:32,310
What's wrong?

230
00:20:33,436 --> 00:20:36,356
You seem kind of down, Satoshi.

231
00:20:38,260 --> 00:20:41,840
You think I don't know anything?

232
00:20:46,280 --> 00:20:47,680
Huh?

233
00:20:51,890 --> 00:20:55,590
But it's fine.

234
00:20:56,660 --> 00:20:58,670
I'll let it go.

235
00:21:04,240 --> 00:21:06,100
Let's start over.

236
00:21:21,870 --> 00:21:22,990
[Are you home?]

237
00:21:22,990 --> 00:21:24,100
[I'm having dinner with Maki,
I'll be back around 10 p.m.]

238
00:21:24,100 --> 00:21:25,280
[Okay, I'll come over.]
[Got it!]

239
00:21:25,280 --> 00:21:34,509
[I broke up with my boyfriend.]

240
00:21:39,633 --> 00:21:41,740
- A latte?
- That sounds good.

241
00:21:41,740 --> 00:21:44,415
- And you?
- Hmm...

242
00:21:58,130 --> 00:22:02,920
[I broke up with my boyfriend.]
[Got it. Haha...]

243
00:22:30,125 --> 00:22:32,140
Kusaka-kun.

244
00:22:32,140 --> 00:22:34,300
Good work today.

245
00:22:34,300 --> 00:22:36,430
Um...

246
00:22:36,430 --> 00:22:38,875
Are you still free tonight?

247
00:22:38,875 --> 00:22:40,825
Huh?

248
00:22:40,825 --> 00:22:43,750
Sorry, I was just surprised earlier.

249
00:22:43,750 --> 00:22:46,145
But I don't have plans tonight,

250
00:22:46,145 --> 00:22:50,455
so if you want, how about a meal?

251
00:22:50,455 --> 00:22:53,120
Oh, but if you can't, that's totally fine!

252
00:22:53,120 --> 00:22:55,505
It's fine. That's great.

253
00:22:55,505 --> 00:22:57,230
I can clock out soon.

254
00:22:57,230 --> 00:22:59,940
Wait for me downstairs.

255
00:22:59,940 --> 00:23:02,730
Oh, it's a promise.

256
00:23:02,730 --> 00:23:04,960
I'll be right there.

257
00:23:04,960 --> 00:23:08,450
♫ Don't let go... ♫

258
00:23:08,450 --> 00:23:11,570
♫ Of my hand ♫

259
00:23:11,570 --> 00:23:18,730
♫ If the rain could dissolve
the two of us like this ♫

260
00:23:18,730 --> 00:23:22,150
♫ We wouldn't... ♫

261
00:23:22,150 --> 00:23:27,660
♫ Need to think about tomorrow ♫

262
00:23:30,960 --> 00:23:35,640
How about... a date tonight?

263
00:23:35,640 --> 00:23:42,650
♫ Hold me close, stay by my side ♫

264
00:23:42,650 --> 00:23:45,495
♫ Don't let go... ♫

265
00:23:45,495 --> 00:23:46,550
I'll walk you.
[Preview]

266
00:23:46,550 --> 00:23:49,788
Kusaka-kun is such a good guy.

267
00:23:49,788 --> 00:23:52,123
Really, a good guy.

268
00:23:52,123 --> 00:23:54,463
What did you do with him?

269
00:23:57,110 --> 00:24:00,000
I won't tell you.
[This drama is fiction.]
